Handful of brussel sprouts, cut in half
2-3 shiitake mushrooms, cut into ribbons
2-3 garlic cloves
Parsley
Linguini
Chili flakes
Â½ c broth
Parmesan cheese
Salt and black pepper to taste

Toast garlic and chili flakes in a medium skillet over low heat.
Add brussel sprouts, mushrooms, and enough broth to cover the bottom of the pan, and raise the heat to high
Squirt a few drops of lemon juice directly onto the sprouts as they cook
Once most of the liquid has reduced, grate in parmesan cheese, add parsley, and finish with lemon broth
Serve over linguini, made using directions from the package
